re feet on the earth's soil and smiles.  She loves the sweet smell of tulips and wanders over to the empty plains outside of Corinth.  She takes her paint-pots and delicately applies colors onto some iris in the field.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sartha>Sartha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/24/01 6:48:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spring in Greece</span><hr size=1> ::Sartha sits quietly in a tree at the edge of the fields, watching Persephone curiously. She had heard of her many times before through the words of her sisters, but had never met her. Now, she was content in watching from a distance, observing:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hypnos>Hypnos </A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/24/01 10:24:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=C:\WINDOWS\Desktop\Stuff\hypnos.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spring in Greece</span><hr size=1> ***Peeks through some of the bushes waking up from a long nap, to see Persephone walking through a meadow. And is happy to have her back from the underworld!*** <p>~*~*~*~*~Thè göd öƒ §|èèp~*~*~*~*~        </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> PersephoneTLJ</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFF33>(5/25/01 5:05:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> ::hums a tune as she paints some flowers.  She notices some rustling in the trees and looks up.  She examines her surroundings.::<br>
<br>
&quot;&quot;Hello?&quot;&quot;  ::Becomes a bit nervous since she is alone.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/26/01 11:21:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> ::The great Poseidon appears by Persephones side in a flash of blue light. He looks around the meadow and then at her.::<br>
<br>
&quot;Hades let you leave the Underworld?&quot;<br>
<br>
::Smiles::<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh yes, I forget this is your time of the year isn't it? I don't think you should be alone. A stranger could come by and kidnap you again.&quot;<br>
<br>
::His laughs echo throughout the field.::  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/utheerinyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Erinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/26/01 1:05:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Appearing. . .</span><hr size=1> The troublesome trio appeared in their usual burst of flames and mist. <br>
<br>
Alecto grinned as she walked past Poseidon and over past Persephone. &quot;Yes, Hades is all alone down there.&quot; She grinned. &quot;Well . . . almost.&quot;<br>
<br>
Megaera walked over to Poseidon and smiled as she dragged her arms around his shoulders playfully. &quot;Well well well, what brings you here Poseidon?&quot;<br>
<br>
Tisiphone merely walked over to Persephone and smiled in greeting to her. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> PersephoneTLJ</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFF33>(5/26/01 6:32:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> ::She looks away from the great god of the sea with sad eyes.  She is very aware of the situation that was created and feels guilty to be torn by two very different worlds::<br>
<br>
::looking at the heavens she lets the sun shine on her face, enjoying the warmth she misses dearly.  She tries not to let the taunts of the Furies and Poseiden get o her.::  Forgive me for saying this dear Uncle, but I do feel safe knowning what happened in the past cannot repeat itself in the future.  For I have one of the most powerful gods watching over me. <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/27/01 1:43:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ::Shadows darken slightly::</span><hr size=1> ::The shadows suddenly darken a bit as suddenly Hades steps out of one them.  He decided to go with a more subtle entrance than splitting the ground open.  He folds his arms, as the arms of his cloak hangs loose on him.  His eyes and cheekbones seeming to be covered by shadow, he turns his gaze to Persephone as he finally cracks a smile, he unfolds his hands, as there is a split Pomegranite in his hands, which he is now munching on::<br>
<br>
&quot;Hello dear.  You've only been gone for a little while and I already miss you.  So I've been bored, and decided to bother my brothers and sisters for a bit.  Tartarus just isn't the same without your presence there.  So, I've kept myself occupied though.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He smirks and continues munching on his Pomegranite as he gazed around and looked at everyone else that seems to have gathered around here:: <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A> at: 5/27/01 1:50:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/30/01 11:20:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spring in Greece</span><hr size=1> ::Poseidon ignored the 3 sisters and looked over to his brother Hades. He walks over to Hades with a smile and extends his hand to him.::<br>
<br>
&quot;Greetings brother. Can't keep away from the wife I see.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sartha>Sartha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/30/01 12:35:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spring in Greece</span><hr size=1> ::continues to watch idly from her tree perch, a brow raised in amusement as the others slowly appear. She juggled with the thought of jumping down and going to join the little chat, then decided against it. Observing was more her style:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> PersephoneTLJ</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFF33>(5/30/01 6:30:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> ::She quickly lowers her face from the sun and looks towards Hades.  Her radient eyes meet his dark ones.  She tries to hide her smile so that the other gods do not see her love for the King of the dead.  Also, knowing that her mother may be close by, Persephone tries to keep her distance from the group.::<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/30/01 7:34:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> ::Hades shoved the pomegranite half in his mouth so he could shake his brother, Poseidon's hand.  After shaking his hand, he released his grip and retrieved the pomegranite from his mouth he then said::<br>
<br>
&quot;Of course I cannot stay away from her, she is one of the lovliest beings I have ever laid eyes on.  The only reason I do is because she has an overbearing Mother that does not know how to let go, and Zeus for some ill-begotten reason agrees with her.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He HOPED Demeter heard that comment.  He continues to gaze at Persephone as a smile perches on his lips he continues to munch on the little seedlings from his pomegranite:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxgoddessaphrodite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xGoddess Aphrodite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/1/01 5:49:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ::appears::  &lt;3</span><hr size=1> ::appears in a golden flash of light, smiling widely::  <br>
<br>
&quot;Who did ya expect?  Mommy Dearest?&quot;<br>
<br>
::Gives a hardy laugh, obviously amuzing herself more than the other gods::<br>
<br>
::Her sheer pink robes float gracefully behind her, proudly revealing her long legs as she walks closer to the group.  She gives a wink to acknowledge the other gods there.  She stops before Persephone and sighs:: <br>
<br>
&quot;Ahhhhhh......Persephone, you are back.  What a great sight to behold on earth.  Must be rough, though, enjoying the days here without someone else to enjoy it with you...::Gives a little sympathetic pout knowing the predictament she is in.  Even the Goddess of Love herself couldn't over-ride this situation of love.::: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/1/01 3:33:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spring in Greece</span><hr size=1> ::Poseidon shakes his head in agreement at his brothers statement.::<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, that's Demeter for you. Zeus, I have a feeling he holds a grudge on us however brother. You and I are his equals in dignity and should be able to get what we want, however his descision should of course be final. But why does he forbid you to have Persephone for yourself only? Because Demeter will stop the produce of the earth? Can he not tell her to let it be and do what it is in her nature to do and be the goddess of the seasons; that it is your right to take whom you please to be your wife or mistress?&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/2/01 4:40:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ::He nods::</span><hr size=1> ::As Aphrodite appeared he gave a respectful nod towards her.  He then turned his focus back to his brother Poseidon::<br>
<br>
&quot;In truth I always found that somewhat hypocritical about him.  But then again what has ever come easy for us?  After all, we spent our first few years in the belly of our Father, Cronus.  Who, I might add, is now resting very nicely down in the lower bowels of Tartarus, as with the rest of our uncles and aunts, the Titans.&quot;  <br>
<br>
::He pounds his foot on the floor a bit to indicate that they are down below.::<br>
<br>
::Hades then whispers in Poseidon's ear very softly::<br>
&quot;I know I got a raw deal, but Call me a fool, call me softhearted, or dare I say, even a romantic; but six-months with Persephone is better than no time at all.  I'll take her any way I can get her.  I know that coming from my lips sounds very strange, and may even diminish my reputation as 'Big Bad Lord of the Underworld', but...&quot;::Shrugs his shoulders::<br>
<br>
::He then gazes at Persephone with a slight smile.:: <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A> at: 6/2/01 4:43:08 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/2/01 10:14:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spring in Greece</span><hr size=1> ::Poseidon nods his head::<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah I know what you mean. When I courted the Gorgon, Medusa I could not keep my hands off of her. I made love to her in Athena's temple without a second thought. Too bad things turned out for her as it did. The gods transforming her into that ugly monster.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/5/01 10:43:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spring in Greece</span><hr size=1> &quot;However brother I will be on my way home. My situation with the gods has forced me into a retreat from them. Home is the place to be in times like this, away from all the nonsense.&quot;<br>
<br>
